(29, 'technical_knowledge', 'VIDEO: RAISING MEAT CHICKENS: The Whole Process', 'broiler, brooding', '2018-06-25', 'busayo', '35963085animal-easter-chick-chicken.jpg', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(17, 17, 17); font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; white-space: pre-wrap;\">This video shows the whole process of Broilers. These chickens are Cornish Cross. From chick to butchering.</span></p><p><iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/1CBfORVzpnU\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p><p><br></p><p><b>Source</b>:<b>The Cook Family Homestead (YouTube)</b></p><h1 id=\"channel-title-container\" class=\"style-scope ytd-c4-tabbed-header-renderer\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; max-height: 9rem; overflow: hidden;\"><br></h1><br>'),
(30, 'technical_knowledge', 'MANAGEMENT OF BROILERS IN HOT WEATHER', 'broiler, management, health,  weather', '2018-06-25', 'busayo', '52613779poultry-farm-1544654_640.jpg', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">A bird could be described as a chemical\r\nfactory which converts feed into energy. In a normal bird, heat production and\r\nloss are balanced and body temperature maintained within close range. Heat\r\nstress therefore sets in when birds are not able to control their body\r\ntemperature anymore and it starts rising. When environmental temperature rises,\r\nthe bird itself get hotter and needs to lose more heat to maintain a constant\r\nbody temperature. The range of temperature (12-24</span><sup style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",=\"\" serif;\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">o</span></sup><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">C) where birds use\r\nno additional energy to maintain their core body temperature is called Thermal\r\nNeutral Zone (TNZ). However, when environmental temperature is above TNZ, birds\r\nneed to dissipate body heat to the surrounding environment in order to maintain\r\nnormal body temperature.</span><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">However, due to lack of sweat\r\nglands, body heat is dissipated to the surrounding environment through\r\nradiation, conduction, convection and evaporation. These methods of heat loss are\r\nknown as sensible heat loss which is effective when temperature ranges 12 to 24</span><sup><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">o</span></sup><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">C.\r\nWhen temperature increases, method of heat loss shifts to evaporative heat\r\nloss, which occurs through panting. Panting removes heat by evaporation of\r\nwater from lungs. It is very effective if the humidity in the environment is\r\nnot too high. The chicken loses 540Kcal by evaporating 1ml of water.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">As water vapour is lost from the\r\nsurface of the lung, heat is lost from the body.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">It is important to note </span><b><i><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">some</span></i></b><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">\r\n</span><b><i><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">conditions\r\nthat are apparent during heat stress</span></i></b><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">. Appetite is depressed by about\r\n12% at temperature of 28</span><sup><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">0</span></sup><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">C. Feed consumption decreases by 1-1.5% for\r\nevery 1</span><sup><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">o</span></sup><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">C above 20</span><sup><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">o</span></sup><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">C and 5% above 32</span><sup><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">o</span></sup><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">C. Birds\r\ndrink more water, 2-4 times than when at normal temperature. There will be an\r\nincrease in muscle activities and more energy is subsequently burnt up.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">There is increase in metabolism\r\nleading to extra waste products which must be removed from the body. Birds\r\ndrink more water to wash these waste products away resulting in loose\r\ndroppings. All these also lead to loss of electrolytes. The overall body\r\nchemistry undergoes change leading to stoppage of heart and death.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><b><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">What\r\nAre The Common Signs Of Heat Stress</span><o:p></o:p></span></b></p><ul><li style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">&nbsp; </span><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Panting</span><o:p></o:p></span></li><li style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Squatting\r\nclose to the ground</span><o:p></o:p></span></li><li style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Wallowing</span><o:p></o:p></span></li><li style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Cannibalism</span><o:p></o:p></span></li><li style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Wet\r\ndroppings</span><o:p></o:p></span></li><li style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal;\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">P</span><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">oor\r\nweight gain</span></span></li></ul><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nline-height:150%;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo1\"><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\"><br></span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><b><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Steps\r\nNeeded To Combat Heat Stress</span><o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nline-height:150%;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo2\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">a)</span><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><b><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Housing Management</span></b><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\"> </span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.25in;text-align:justify;line-height:\r\n150%\"><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">This is foundational\r\nand paramount to combating heat stress that could be prevalent in regions like\r\nNigeria. </span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nline-height:150%;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo5\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\nSymbol\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\"></span><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">The\r\ndirection of the pen should be East-West. This is to minimize direct access of\r\nsunlight to the long side of the pen.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nline-height:150%;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo5\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\nSymbol\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\"></span><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Side\r\nwall should be maximum of 2- blocks. </span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nline-height:150%;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo5\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\nSymbol\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\"></span><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">The\r\nplanting of tall trees along the long axis of the pen will ensure a better\r\nweather condition.</span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nline-height:150%;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo5\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\nSymbol\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\"></span><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">The\r\nroof should be painted with white wash to reflect heat radiations. Thatching of\r\nroof is another good alternative. </span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">I\r\nhad experiences with a farmer who lost matured broilers to heat stress because\r\nof poor ventilation arising from poor housing. Such loss could be colossal. We\r\nhad to reduce the stocking density and make holes at different points along the\r\nside wall which was initially too high.</span><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">&nbsp; </span><i><font face=\"Times New Roman, serif\"><o:p></o:p></font></i></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nline-height:150%;mso-list:l5 level1 lfo6\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\nSymbol\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\"></span><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Give\r\n10% extra floor space. It is good for farmers to be proactive and not act based\r\non what you have read in books alone. </span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nline-height:150%;mso-list:l5 level1 lfo6\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\nSymbol\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\"></span><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">You\r\ncan increase the rate of air movement over the birds by providing fans. This\r\nwill help removed trapped heats from birds. </span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nline-height:150%;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo2\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif;=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">b)</span><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></b><!--[endif]--><b><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Water Management</span><o:p></o:p></span></b></p><ul><li style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Farmer\r\nmust ensure that clean and cool water is supplied regularly</span><o:p></o:p></span></li><li style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Water\r\ntanks should be covered with wet gunny bags to avoid direct exposure to sun</span><o:p></o:p></span></li><li style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Increase\r\nnumber of drinkers by 25% to ensure that there is an equal access to water by\r\nbirds at all times.</span><o:p></o:p></span></li><li style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Provide\r\nelectrolytes with vitamin C in water. </span><o:p></o:p></span></li><li style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Do\r\nnot withhold drinking water for long when vaccine is provided through drinking\r\nwater</span><o:p></o:p></span></li><li style=\"line-height: 150%;\"><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Protect\r\nwater tank from direct sunlight.</span><o:p></o:p></span></li></ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nline-height:150%;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo2\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif;=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">c)</span><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></b><!--[endif]--><b><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Feed\r\nManagement</span><o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nline-height:150%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\nSymbol\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\"></span><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Pelletized\r\nfeed increases physical density resulting in higher uptake of nutrients at a\r\ngiven volume of feed. </span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nline-height:150%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\nSymbol\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\"></span><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",serif\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Withdraw\r\nfeed 4-5 hours prior to the anticipated time of peak temperature.</span><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">&nbsp; </span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nline-height:150%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbo